<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 6:41PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Catoosa and
north central Whitfield Counties through 715 PM EDT...
At 641 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Graysville, or near
Ringgold, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds 40 to 50 mph and up to penny sized hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Oglethorpe, Varnell, Cohutta, Graysville and Indian Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for northwestern
Georgia.</instruction>
